706753f-b.text:
Shore Boulevard, east from West End Avenue, along
the shore of Sheepshead Bay. The views show operations
being conducted by the W. P. A. in the widening of the
thoroughfare. A new bulkhead line had to be constructed
and part of the bay filled in to a depth of about twenty
feet. On the north side of Sheepshead Bay (left) is
Emmons Avenue, which is also heing widened as part of the
circumferential highway system which will girt the city.
